news.title: PE investment in real estate up 40% in Apr-Sep to $2.8 billion: Report
news.para: As per the report, investments by foreign investors contributed around 78 per cent to the total inflow in the first half of this fiscal, reflecting their strong confidence in Indian real estate.

news.title: Life in a 95-sq-foot apartment! How tinier living spaces are taking over Tokyo
news.para: With its high property prices and the world's most populous metropolitan area, Tokyo has long been known for small accommodations.

news.title: Gujarat: Sale deeds pile up at registration offices
news.para: This backlog arose because of a clarification that the state government had issued three months ago on the procedures to be followed for collection of stamp duty in case the property belonged to an old co-operative housing society.

news.title: Kolkata civic body departments team up to bring new properties under tax net
news.para: This tie-up will fetch the civic body substantial revenue by bringing the new constructions under the property tax net.

news.title: PAP moves Bombay HC, challenges land regularisation in Cidco area
news.para: The GR was issued on February 25, 2022, to regularize the mass scale illegal houses by allowing 30% discount in Cidco’s reserved price for plots up to 200 sq metres and 60% for 201 sq metres to 500 sq metres area.

news.title: Telangana to auction 19 properties in 10 districts
news.para: ​Apart from properties in and around Hyderabad which would be e-auctioned, the others across the state will be done via physicial bidding process.

news.title: Ambuja Cements gets shareholders' nod for raising Rs 20,000 crore from Adani group firm
news.para: Resolutions to appoint Adani Group Chairman Gautam Adani, his son Karan Adani and two directors and four independent directors on the board of Ambuja Cements were also approved by the shareholders.

news.title: Registered construction workers to get Rs 4.75 lakh per head to build home: Maharashtra minister
news.para: Of the Rs4.75 lakh, Rs2.75 lakh would be allotted under the Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojana. The additional Rs2 lakh would be provided by the state labour department.

news.title: Decide senior citizen's complaint within six months: HC directs MahaRERA
news.para: The Bombay High Court has directed the Maharashtra Real Estate Regulatory Authority (MahaRERA) to decide expeditiously, within six months, a complaint filed before it by a senior citizen, which has been pending for two years.

news.title: MahaRERA orders Cornerstone to pay compensation over change of flat plan and delay
news.para: However, the developer failed to allot the flats or enter into an agreement of sale and amended the sanctioned plans without consent and changed it to 2 BHK flats measuring 900 sq ft.

news.title: Rajasthan HC notice to government, RERA over empowering architects to issue CC
news.para: The court sought a reply from the Rajasthan RERA, urban development and housing department and state government.

news.title: Navi Mumbai: Directors of National Builders get clean chit in land usurp case
news.para: Directors MC Sunny (62) and Sijo Sunny (35) have recently procured the chargesheet's court certified copy, by paying the applicable court fees of Rs 1568 as per Rs4 per page.

news.title: Consumer forum upholds six months jail & Rs 25,000 fine to Nagpur builder
news.para: Band had launched a farmhouses scheme named “Swapna Srushti” at Hingna spread over eight hectares. She promised all amenities like a swimming pool, health and sports clubs, streetlights, shops and restaurants.

news.title: Vietnam arrests real estate tycoon over financial frauds
news.para: Truong My Lan, chairwoman of Ho Chi Minh City-based Van Thinh Phat Holdings Group, was accused of illegally issuing bonds to raise trillions of dong (tens of millions of dollars) from investors during the 2018-2019 period, the Ministry of Public Security said in a news release on Saturday.

news.title: Construction waste recycling facility at Cunchelim: Goa environment minister
news.para: “The site has been identified. It is government property and we plan to set up a construction and demolition waste recycling facility plant there,” he said.
